description._content: Bain News Service,, publisher. Karl Franz Josef in Budapest [between ca. 1914 and ca. 1915] 1 negative : glass ; 5 x 7 in. or smaller. Notes: Title from data provided by the Bain News Service on the negative. Photograph shows Karl Franz Joseph (Charles I of Austria) (1887-1922) with soldiers next to train during World War I. (Source: Flickr Commons project, 2012) Forms part of: George Grantham Bain Collection (Library of Congress). Subjects: World War, 1914-1918. Format: Glass negatives. Rights Info: No known restrictions on publication.
